description: This subseries contains more than 17,000 items and consists primarily of photographs of artists and artworks, but also includes images of other cultural figures and groupings of photographs by art genre. Szeemann exhibited work by many, but not all of the artists in the subseries; the exhibition titles are referenced when they were identified by Szeemann. (See Subseries IV.A. for more photographic documentation of exhibitions.) Among the artists who are particularly well represented in this subseries are: Joseph Beuys, James Lee Byars, Michael Heizer, Edward Kienholz, Piotr Kowalski, Wolfgang Laib, Mario Merz, Otto Muehl, Hermann Nitsch, Claes Oldenburg, Sigmar Polke, Royden Rabinowitch, Markus Raetz, Armand Schulthess, Richard Serra, Kieth Sonnier, Niele Toroni, Cy Twombly and Ben Vautier.
